<br>
Max HPs aren't that important since neither class CHs.  It is only a factor if you need to heal before the fight is over.  Regens are more mana efficient (as long as you use the healing) than even CC.   With epic they can land a 50% slow fairly fast on most XP mobs.  With their damage shields, ATK buffs (intended ones and exploitable ones), and innate ATK bonus they will significantly outdamage a paladin on live mobs, and will possibly continue to do so on undead ones.<br>
<br>
Add in sow (dont need to watch crappy SoL animations to run fast , like with holy steed), invis, harmony, and snare and rangers have every tool you could reasonably expect to have to solo.  Add in tracking and outdoor hunting becomes much more efficient.<br>
<br>
In *pure* soloing (no 2 boxing with an enchanter, e.g.) I think a ranger is more flexible and does it faster than a paladin in most situations.  A paladin's advantage is survivability.<br>
<br>
